The paper discusses techniques for estimating the approximate ranks of large data matrices, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and data-related applications. The methods proposed in the paper are based on spectral densities, which are commonly used in physics and have been applied to matrix analysis. Therefore, the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
